

### This is just a practice build and a reference for future full stack builds.

## MERN stack

Node.js
npm
React
mongoose.db
Express server


## Steps to build from "ground up":

1. Set up root folder:

- >mkdir {name_of_project}
- >cd {name_of_project}
- >type nul> server.js
- >code .


2. VS code terminal: (Ctr `)

- >npm init -y  // sets up package.json file
- >npm install express //set up your required dependencies
- >type nul> .gitignore // include "/node_modules" within
- >git init //create repo in the root folder to avoid any snags later 

2. server.js initialization:

const express = require("express");
const app = express();
const {port} = 8000;


app.list(port, ()=>{
    console.log(`App is listening on port ${port}`);
})

>nodemon server.js

--check localhost://8000